  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education Management Improvement Practices (EMIP) Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Stakeholder Engagement: Ownership must be built within the institution to ensure the sustainability of reform projects. This entails involving all parties in the planning and implementation stages. Whenever possible, projects should also have local leadership
Capacity building of District Education Officers and school administrative officers on transparency and accountability on the use of public resources: Selected officers from DEOs and Schools will be trained on stakeholder engagement and consultations in the use of public resources. The training will focus on areas of stakeholder engagement skills such as negotiations skills, communication skills, structures of engagement, citizen rights in education management  and reporting.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To empower community stakeholders such as women, girls, parents, chiefs, queen mothers, community based organisations to demand for accountability and transparency from duty bearers such as educational/school authorities in the Amansie West District. 
To build the capacity of educational/school authorities on community stakeholder engagement to increase transparency and accountability within Ghana Education Service in the Amansie West District.
To reduce the number of perceived corruption cases in the Amamsie West Directorate of Ghana Education Service</narrative>
  </description>
